The paper proposes a quantum version of a classical protocol for transmitting data over a noisy channel, which suggests that it could fall under the category of "Quantum Physics" (cs.ET). The use of quantum teleportation and superdense coding also indicates that it could be related to "Information Theory" (cs.IT). The paper also deals with the issue of reliability in the presence of noise, which could be relevant to "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The use of process algebra to show correctness suggests that it could be related to "Programming Languages" (cs.PL) or "Logic in Computer Science" (cs.LO).
